      "content": "wait, you said \"the consensus among sociologists\" is that it's dangerous... that seems a bit one-sided. aren't there plenty of scholars who argue that without some form of national identity, you can't actually have a functioning democracy or a social safety net? it feels like you're dismissing the argument for social cohesion entirely.",
